jQuery.ui.autoWidthFit is a element width adjuster.
See the demo below what this plugin can do.
Imagine this works with masonry layout things like below plugin.
http://isotope.metafizzy.co/
works on jQuery 1.6.2. IE6/7/8 supported too.

Usage:

$('#test').autoWidthFit({
	widthchange: function(){
		log('widthchange event fired.');
	},
	firstwidthchange: function(){
		log('firstwidthchange event fired.');
	}
});

Demo:

basic
http://dl.dropbox.com/u/268240/gitHubDemos/jQuery.ui.autoWidthFit/index.html

with isotope (NOTE: you need license fee to use isotope for commercial use)
